The paper discusses a common mathematical representation of data sets that applies across a wide range of applications and technologies, including spreadsheets, databases, matrices, and graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.IT (information theory), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.SI (social and information networks). However, given the focus on databases and data processing systems, cs.DB is the most likely category.
